.TH FOSSIL 1 "July 2026" "fossil 0.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
fossil \- structure-aware compression that explains how it rebuilds your files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fossil
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ args ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fossil
cuts a file into 4\ KB blocks and runs a handful of small models on each one,
keeping whichever output comes out smallest. The choice is written into the
.I .fossil
so
.B "fossil explain"
can read it back, block by block.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BI "pack " "<input> [output]"
Compress a file or directory into a
.IR .fossil .
With no input, packs the clipboard.
.TP
.B lift
Fossilize whatever is on the clipboard, then copy the
.I .fossil
back to it.
.TP
.BI "unpack " "<file.fossil> [output]"
Restore the original (verifies the CRC).
.TP
.BI "list " "<dir.fossil>"
List the files inside a directory fossil.
.TP
.BI "take " "<file.fossil> [path]"
Pull one file out to stdout. For a directory fossil, name the inner
.IR path ;
it is decoded from its own segment without touching the rest of the archive, and
its stored CRC is checked unless
.BR --trust .
.TP
.BI "mount " "<dir.fossil> <mountpoint>"
Mount a directory fossil as a live filesystem (unix). Reads decode on demand,
writes are staged in memory, and changes are written back on unmount.
.TP
.BI "inspect " "<file>"
Per-block analysis: entropy, model, savings.
.TP
.BI "map " "<file>"
Entropy heatmap, or block models for a
.IR .fossil .
.TP
.BI "explain " "<file.fossil>"
The reconstruction recipe.
.TP
.BI "verify " "<file.fossil>"
Check a fossil's CRC without unpacking. Exits nonzero if corrupt.
.TP
.B update
Reinstall the latest fossil from git.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "pack --lossy" [=bits]
Quantize by dropping the low bits of each byte (3 by default).
.TP
.B pack --best-effort
Pack already-compressed inputs losslessly instead of refusing.
.TP
.B pack --images-only
Only apply lossy to raw image formats.
.TP
.B pack --verify
Verify the round-trip before writing.
.TP
.B pack --fast
Skip the slow models for faster packing
.TP
.B update --man
Install and/or update man pages for fossil
.TP
.B update --completions
Install and/or update completions for fish, zsh, and bash
.TP
.B lift --reveal
After packing the clipboard, reveal the
.I .fossil
in the file manager so it is easy to drag elsewhere.
.TP
.B unpack --trust
Skip the CRC check on unpack.
.TP
.B take --trust
Skip the per-file CRC check when taking from a directory fossil.
.TP
.B mount --verbose
Show a rolling display of recent filesystem events while serving.
.TP
.B mount --log
Print every filesystem event line-by-line, for diagnosing.
.TP
.BI "explain --block " N
Deep-dive a single block.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Compress a directory:
.B fossil pack src/ archive
.TP
Fossilize the clipboard:
.B fossil lift
.TP
Restore an archive:
.B fossil unpack archive.fossil out
.TP
Check integrity:
.B fossil verify archive.fossil
.TP
Extract one file from a directory fossil:
.B fossil take archive.fossil src/main.rs
.TP
Mount a directory fossil:
.B fossil mount archive.fossil mnt/
.TP
Pipe directly into fossil:
.B cat foo.png | fossil pack > foo.fossil
